<paragraph id="F32D5F2DFFEAFFA9EDF2A629FE07F811" blockId="20.[151,1437,1362,1963]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="C1E6833FFFEAFFA9EDF2A629FEFFF8A1" bold="true" box="[199,273,1794,1819]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">Notes.</emphasis>
This species was described based on an unknown number of male and female specimens deposited in the 
<mcCollectionCode id="26BF3AA2FFEAFFA9EDF5A60CFEFFF885" box="[192,273,1831,1855]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="20" pageNumber="493" type="Museum">USNM</mcCollectionCode>
collection. A male cotype is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="2C29E18FFFEAFFA9EE07A60DFC77F885" box="[818,921,1830,1855]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">lectotype</typeStatus>
to fix the identity of the species. Our concept of the species is based on information provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="970322DCFFEAFFA9EE3CA661FC48F8D9" author="Baker, C. F." box="[777,934,1866,1891]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493" pagination="57 - 71" refId="ref17954" refString="Baker, C. F. (1924) The genus Makilingia (Jassoidea) in the Philippines. Philippine Journal of Science, 24 (1), 57 - 71." type="journal article" year="1924">Baker (1924)</bibRefCitation>
. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="349224AEFFEAFFA9E9E4A660FAA4F8D9" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1924" box="[1233,1354,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis id="C1E6833FFFEAFFA9E9E4A660FAA4F8D9" box="[1233,1354,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">M. lineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the coloration of the head but differs in having the wedge-shaped black marking on the crown broader and the forewing clavus mostly black.
</paragraph>
